						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying near the house of Muḷki Pāṭil.</p>						

						<p>1508 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, the purport of which is not clear, is dated Śaka [1430], Subhānu, Bhādrapada śu 10. Monday corresponding to A.D. 1521, September 4, Monday. However, the cyclic year was Vishu, not Subhānu. Seems to record the gift of an <hi rend="italic">aṟavaṭige</hi> by Timmapa-nāyaka. Kulakaraṇi Kēsava comosed the record.</p>						

						</summary>
